summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeBuild irresistibly thick and lifted lashes with every stroke of the longwear FENTY Hella Thicc Volumizing Mascara. The ultra-creamy, ultra-black formula features a tapered brush that coats and loads every lash for an effect that looks outrageous yet feels weightless.

reviews.headline: Glamorous Bottle with Amazing Results
reviews.comments: When I first got the product I was a little worried since the brush was so big and it looked like the mascara would apply clumpy like similar brands I've used before. However, I was extremely shocked since it applied so seamlessly that it rivals the results of my favorite mascara. With just one application it looked wonderful and lasted all day. It is a little stubborn to remove but microcelluar waterproof water works wonders. I would definitely recommend and buy this once I run out :)

reviews.headline: panda effect
reviews.comments:
I got brown mascara, and the color is not giving brown. It's more like not as black. This is not the bad part, a lot of brands do this, which is sad but okay. The bad part is it smudges a lot. Just an hour after applying, I have dark under eyes. Also, because I have hooded eyes, the ends of lashes leave dark dots on my upper lid. It's easy to remove, just with micellar water. Doesn't irritate. But overall, I don't like it. No one wants to wipe away dark circles during the day.
Maybe black one is not the same, but brown one is bad.
I don't see how I can add a photo.

reviews.headline: Not the Fenty quality I expected
reviews.comments:
I bought this mascara to try something new, hoping for it to be very dark (shade is called "cuz I'm black") and needed it visible for a play I was in. Credit where it's due: it is dark and visible. Unfortunately that's it for the pros. 

The product coming out of the tube is clumpy after just 5 uses over 3 weeks. If I sweat at all, even from the car to an air conditioned building, it transfers to my under eye, where it has much better staying power and is difficult to remove. I didn't think I needed a waterproof for 3 hours of wear at a time! I live in Texas, and it's June, so there's no way to test if it smears when it's cold out. 

My recommendation is to go with a different mascara. I threw this one away immediately after the play ended.

reviews.headline: dangit
reviews.comments: After I applied this mascara I was so excited about it because it made my sparse lashes look so nice! But then a few hours later I found that it was transferring black to my lower lash line area! :( but here's the weird thing, it's hard to get off even with makeup remover.  Not sure how it can transfer over a few hours of time but remain on with makeup remover?

reviews.headline: My go-to
reviews.comments: Love this mascara! I have super sensitive eyes and can't use many mascaras, but this one doesn't bother me! and it lasted me through my long work shifts outside in summer heat when sweating a ton!

faceoff_positive.comments:
As an expert, I am excited to share my positive review of the Fenty Beauty Hella Thicc Volumizing Mascara in the shade "Cuz I'm Black". This mascara is an exceptional product that delivers amazing results, making it a must-have for any makeup lover.

One of the standout features of this mascara is the length of the applicator. It is long and flexible, which makes it easy to acquire both volume and length for your lashes. The applicator is also designed to reach even the smallest lashes in the inner corners of your eyes, making your lashes look fuller and longer than ever before.

The shade "Cuz I'm Black" is another highlight of this mascara. It is a rich, deep black that makes your lashes stand out and complement any makeup look. It is perfect for those who want dramatic and bold lashes.

One of the most impressive things about this mascara is its waterproof formula. It can withstand heat and water, which means you can wear it all day and not have to worry about it smudging or running. This makes it perfect for those hot summer days or a night out dancing.

Another great feature of the Fenty Beauty Hella Thicc Volumizing Mascara is its long-lasting formula. It stays put for hours without flaking or smudging, which means you won't have to worry about touch-ups throughout the day. This is a game-changer for those who want a mascara that can withstand a long day.

Overall, I highly recommend the Fenty Beauty Hella Thicc Volumizing Mascara in "Cuz I'm Black". It delivers amazing results, has a fantastic applicator, and is both waterproof and long-lasting. It is a must-have for anyone looking to elevate their lash game.
faceoff_positive.headline: Buy it NOW, Run

faceoff_negative.comments:
The outside packaging of this product is nice.  The actual container the mascara is in is also nice because it is shaped differently and has some weight to it.  It is also easy to hold.  When I first applied the mascara, it started a little clumpy but I thought maybe just because it is brand new that this was the case.  I tried to wipe it off on the rim of the container a little.  Once it wasn't as lumpy it did go on my lashes pretty nicely without having much clumps.  I also did not have to reapply multiple coats for it to lengthen my lashes which also saved time.  I put it on one side of my face just to compare it to the side without any mascara and it definitely made a difference.
I wore it around the house the entire day and it lasted for the most part, except there was a little black that had accumulated underneath my eye.  My other mascaras wear very well throughout the day and I would be worried this one might run somewhat and I would need to keep checking the mirror.  By the end of the day, my lashes didn't seem as black or volumized as they initially were.  I guess this is also not waterproof because as soon as my face got wet, it really ran down my face. The good news is that it was very easy to get off with makeup remover and did not leave a residue on my lashes.  Overall, it went on smoothly and looked good at first but if you are planning to wear it for an entire day I don't know if this is the product for you.  I will try it one more time when I am going out somewhere for a short time period but not for an important event.  I am going to stick with my Thrive Causemetics mascara for now but I do appreciate the invite to try this mascara.
faceoff_negative.headline: I would not buy this product again
